Here is how you can create an OkHttpClient POST request with the provided cURL in Java:

import okhttp3.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Initialize OkHttpClient
        OkHttpClient client = new OkHttpClient();

        // Create the JSON body
        String jsonBody = "{"
                + "\"sellerSeq\":\"000123456789\","
                + "\"packageName\":\"com.samsung.android.sample\","
                + "\"requestDate\":\"20230615\","
                + "\"continuationToken\":\"e5ec039730164c50277f9a231b74c1b6e035d9184160d8b3d6b3de1f62691328fbe4c0c4863da52b3bcecef44a4c7acb974c674728c3cb173cb339bd41783f2c\""
                + "}";

        // Create the request body
        RequestBody body = RequestBody.create(
                jsonBody, MediaType.parse("application/json; charset=utf-8"));

        // Build the request
        Request request = new Request.Builder()
                .url("https://devapi.samsungapps.com/iap/seller/orders")
                .post(body)
                .addHeader("Authorization", "Bearer <your-access-token>")
                .addHeader("service-account-id", "<your-service-account-id>")
                .addHeader("content-type", "application/json")
                .build();

        // Execute the request
        try (Response response = client.newCall(request).execute()) {
            if (response.isSuccessful()) {
                // Get and print the response
                System.out.println(response.body().string());
            } else {
                System.out.println("Request failed: " + response.code());
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Explanation:

1. OkHttpClient: Used to send requests and receive responses.


2. RequestBody: The JSON body is created with the necessary data.


3. Request: The POST request is built, adding the necessary headers and the JSON body.


4. Response: The response from the API is printed if the request is successful.



You need to replace <your-access-token> and <your-service-account-id> with the actual values.

